<br>
Here's what it comes down to:  those who say wizards are underpowered DO NOT KNOW HOW TO PLAY THE CLASS.<br>
<br>
We're not even remotely close to underpowered.  Between concussion and the epic skin, I can do disgusting amounts of damage (like more than a 60 rogue using duellist) and never be aggro for more than a few seconds.  We can quad kite, we can crowd control, we can evac, we can stun (which is hugely valuable, when used properly), and all the rest.<br>
<br>
Melees do more damage than us ONLY when you're talking about sustained damage rate over a period of several hours.  But in terms of mob-must-die-right-now-no-questions-asked damage, nobody can even come close.  And OMG the bane spells.. everyone used to believe rogues were the key to velious uber mobs, but lemme tell you, nothing puts em down quite like a bane.<br>
<br>
To you young wizards out there who read the whine posts on this board, just be patient, put in your time, and get yourselves to level 60.  Trust me, it's well worth the effort. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/5/01 8:58:36 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grim3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Day, Same old Whining</span><hr size=1> Good to hear you believe Wizards are not underpowered when they are level 60 with both bane spells, the epic, and concussion quests done.  Great news, bud.  Now about those previous 59 levels.... <p><IMG SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg" ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/6/01 7:20:52 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Day, Same old Whining</span><hr size=1> Thank you for verifying that for me.  I've always felt that that was my greatest power - being the saving grace when the cleric goes, &quot;umm, I'm oom,&quot; and the tank just went berserk cause an add popped out of nowhere.<br>
When it's all said and done, and I get a group that works well, something ALWAYS happens where i have to burn if we're together long enough.  And I LOVE it.  I picked a wizard because I wanted to kill stuff.  I wanted to be able to go FLASH and there's nothing left but a corpse.  2.5 seconds, dead MOB.  I actually go back to Blackburrow and do train cleanup for fun just for that reason every now and then.  knowing that I'll always have that ability to kill something fast, I'll be here till lvl 60... if EQ doesn't shut down before then.<br>
&lt;/babble&gt; <p><br>Aniar Orrenson
<br>Wizard of the 29th Season
<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath
<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uthecobalwizard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TheCobalWizard</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/6/01 8:35:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Day, Same old Whining</span><hr size=1> /cheer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umaylorcoronis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maylor Coronis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/6/01 11:14:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Day, Same old Whining</span><hr size=1> i have to agree with Grim...to a point.  I don't think it's that wizars are underpowered, however...it's that tanks get so twinked now-a-days that wizard damage at anything under level 60 is no where near comparison.  And since I am a casual gamer, I really don't think that I'll ever hit 60, get my banes, and raid everyday.  Hell, I'll be happy to make it far enough just to see the Planes.  I just wish Verant would make it a little easier for the casual gamer.  I know that would throw everything out of whack, but I have a job, school, and a life outside of my PC.  I can't afford to play 4 hours a day.  Heck i'm lucky if i get in 4-5 hours a week.  I don't want an uber damage upgrade, i don't want a pet, i don't want group buffs.  I want to be able to play a little at a time and not be totally surpassed by someone who can twink the hell out of their alts because they have 30 hours a week to blow off.  (i'm sure it sounds like i'm asking for a nerf, but that's not it either...i'm not sure how to fix this whole scenario with out nerfing something somewhere)  oh well....maybe when SW: Galaxies comes out all this class balance BS will be gone.  And fun will be the main focus for people, not damage/delay...not efficency(sp)...not who has what uber weapon...FUN <p><font color=#3399FF>Maylor Conornis<br/>
30th High Elven Wizard
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/6/01 12:18:47 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Day, Same old Whining</span><hr size=1> I wonder if they made a server (or account structure) for EQ2 that was &quot;for casual gamers&quot;, that had a limited number of hours per month, to enforce it being for casual gamers like you and me... maybe 20 to 30 hours a month max (5-7 hours a week) that had MOB HPs lessened by a small percent, like 10%, so that you wouldn't have to get as big of raids together to get the big things, and so that we'd be more likely to see the high-end game.<br>
It's a bit easier to level, so you level in fewer hours of gaming, but because you're limited to a number of hours per month per account, you're probably going to level no faster in real time compared to the people who play 30 hours a week.<br>
