Craar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/18/01 7:09:54 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:New Day, Same old Whining</span><hr size=1> For those of you out there, the boost wizards get at 57 is more useful than the one at 60(if you can get the spells).<br>
<br>
It may not SEEM like a huge upgrade, but going from previous draughts to draught of ice IS a significant upgrade(in Kunark, not Velious).  683 damage for previous draughts, 726 damage for draught of ice per cast.  It REALLY adds up if you cast 4 times since it's the same mana and casting time.<br>
<br>
<br>
But, there's other issues than those mentioned earlier in this thread.  If you sit in OS shouting for a group, and DON'T give up, and keep trying, you will find that the more time you spend there, the easier it becomes to get a group as you level up.  If you give up, go off soloing, then come back and expect to get groups, forget it, it probably won't happen.  If people know you, and from experience know that you are a wizard that is a benefit to your group, you get groups easier and easier.  The problem is that most don't stick with it to let others know you can play your class well.<br>
<br>
Back before Velious, I went to OS at level 51, shouted for groups, and after a while, I started getting them within 30 minutes of my shouting.  Then Velious came out, and I went off to explore(I find exploring new zones more fun than sitting in one camp for 4+ hours).  A few months later, I went back to OS, and couldn't get a group because most of the people I had grouped with moved on to Velious.  I just couldn't get a group.<br>
<br>
So, I got annoyed, and stuck it out, explored some more, got guild groups here and there, and explored some of the other zones in Velious.  And again, I found that I wasn't getting groups, until I just decided to stick with one zone, and NOT hop around.  As the people in each zone get to know me, and my play style, I get groups easier and easier.  They KNOW that not all wizards suck, but they have seen too many wizards who cast once, twice, or three times, then sit down, and don't make their presence KNOWN.  I'll burn down a mob or two(and they see the mobs drop quick when I do), and I'll med out on others.  They can feel and see the difference I bring.  It's about perception, and letting others SEE that we add to a group.<br>
<br>
What's better, doing 2k damage to each mob you face, or 6k damage to every third mob.  The first will be more of a steady contribution, but the 6k will drop the mob, and make your presence FELT.  Who will they remember of these two when melees are KNOWN for their steady damage, and they can't see the damage we do with our spells.  They get disciplines, and we all SEE critical hits, and all the amazing damage output that discs can add over a short period.  Wizards are about amazing damage over a short period, but it's not seen when we kick it into gear, unless we make a point of it.<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 59 Wizard<br>
Bloodguard of Souls<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
